<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-241-482  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 241 482.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>MacWEEK  March 13 1990 v4 n10 p6(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Coastal Associates Publishing L.P. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Descartes puts business database records on map. (Intermap'sbusiness mapping program) (product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Norr, Henry.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Intermap Inc. (product introduction).andO;Product:   Descartes (Geographic information system) (product introduction).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionData Base Management SystemsMapsGeographic Information Systems.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>By Henry NorrandM;Lyme, N.H.andP;  -- Descartes, a business mapping program that promises &quot;abreakthrough in ease of use, combined with power comparable to advancedminicomputer-based systems,&quot; will make its debut at next month's MacworldExpo.andM;Designed to help market researchers, advertising planners and other businessdecision makers link demographic and economic data, the $995 programintegrates multilayer map views with a built-in relational database,according to its developer, Intermap Inc.andP;  Clicking on areas, lines or pointson a map allows immediate access to records stored in the database, Intermapsaid.andP;  Built-in tools let users import information from databases andspreadsheets and query the data on the basis of field values, user-definedformulas, equal intervals or quantiles.andM;Jerry Lopes, director of market research at the Maryland Casualty Co. inBaltimore, said the program's developers have &quot;a very good feel for whatbusiness users really need.andP;  The best thing about it,&quot; he said, &quot;is that youcan access data at any geographical level without fiddling around withboundary files.&quot;andM;The package, which is to be released this summer, will ship with state andcounty boundaries with current demographic data; ZIP code locationinformation; and map data for major cities and interstate highways.andP;  Thepublisher will also offer Snap-In Data, a series of optional files containinggeographic, demographic and economic data from leading information vendors.andM;Descartes' customizable maps can range in size up to 8 by 5 feet.andP;  Theprogram supports zooming from the national level to a scale of 1 inch equalto every 6 feet.andM;The program was developed by Dwight Aspinwall, designer of DartmouthCollege's on-line, video-linked Macintosh Training Seminars, and JeffreyDoyle, a former remote sensing and mapping specialist for the U.S.andP;  ArmyCorps of Engineers.andM;Intermap Inc. is located at 13 Dartmouth College Highway, Lyme, N.H.andP;  03748;(603) 795-4751.andP;  n</TEXT></DOC>